content:
  - Name:           binutils
  - Version:        2.40
  - Release:        1%{?dist}
  - Summary:        A set of tools for working with object code. GPLv3+
  - 
  - License:        GPLv3+
  - URL:            https://www.gnu.org/software/binutils/
  - 
  - Source0:        binutils-%{version}.tar.xz
  - 
  - BuildRequires:  zlib-devel
  - BuildRequires:  bzip2-devel
  - BuildRequires:  libtool
  - BuildRequires:  gmp-devel
  - BuildRequires:  mpfr-devel
  - BuildRequires:  gcc
  - BuildRequires:  make
  - BuildRequires:  texinfo
  - 
  - %description
  - The binutils package contains a collection of binary utilities, including:
  - 
  - * ld - The GNU linker.
  - * as - The GNU assembler.
  - * addr2line - Converts addresses into filenames and line numbers.
  - * ar - Creates, modifies, and extracts from archives.
  - * nm - Lists symbols from object files.
  - * objcopy - Copies and translates object files.
  - * objdump - Displays information from object files.
  - * ranlib - Generates an index to the contents of an archive.
  - * readelf - Displays detailed information about ELF format files.
  - * size - Lists the section sizes of an object or archive file.
  - * strings - Lists the printable strings in a file.
  - * strip - Discards symbols and other data from object files.
  - * c++filt - Demangles C++ symbols.
  - 
  - %prep
  - %setup -q -n binutils-%{version}
  - 
  - %build
  - ./configure --prefix=/usr --enable-shared --disable-nls --with-system-zlib
  - make %{?_smp_mflags}
  - 
  - %install
  - make install DESTDIR=%{buildroot}
  - rm -f %{buildroot}/usr/share/info/dir
  - 
  - %files
  - %license COPYING*
  - /usr/bin/*
  - /usr/lib64/*
  - /usr/share/man/man1/*
  - /usr/share/info/*
  - 
  - %changelog
  - * %{date} Dan Carpenter <DanC403@gmail.com> - 2.40-1
  - - Initial package build.
